ribers (millions)** | 10.3 | 5.0 | 8.9 | 4.4 | 2.3 |\n| **Starlink ARPU ($/month)** | $66 | $86 | $81 | $91 | $99 |\n\n---\n\n### **5. Cost & Expense Breakdown (2025)**\n| **Expense Category** | **2025** | **2024** | **2023** |\n|----------------------|----------|----------|----------|\n| **Cost of Revenue** | $5,921 million | $4,768 million | $2,786 million |\n| **Research & Development** | $575 million | $453 million | $381 million |\n| **SG&A** | $468 million | $333 million | $233 million |\n| **Depreciation & Amortization** | $2,376 million | $1,508 million | $884 million |\n| **Share-Based Compensation** | $369 million | $296 million | $249 million |\n| **Capital Expenditures** | $4,178 million | $3,498 million | $2,455 million |\n\n---\n\n### **6. Q1 2026 Expense Drivers**\n- **Cost of Revenue** increased by $437 million (+36.0%) due to:\n  - Higher depreciation ($276 million) from satellite launches.\n  - Increased ground operations, installation, and warranty costs.\n- **R&D** increased by $82 million (+66.7%) for next-gen satellites and ground equipment.\n- **SG&A** increased to support international expansion.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Growth Drivers (MD&A Commentary)**\n- **Consumer Revenue**: Driven by **104.7% subscriber growth** in Q1 2026, partially offset by a **22.9% decline in ARPU** due to international expansion and lower-priced plans.\n- **Enterprise & Government Revenue**: Growth in **aviation, maritime, mobility, and government connectivity** (e.g., Starshield contracts).\n- **Profitability**: Scale efficiencies from LEO satellite constellations and verticalized supply chain.\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\nThe **Connectivity segment** (primarily Starlink) shows:\n1. **Explosive revenue growth** (96% in 2024, 50% in 2025, 32% Q1 2026).\n2. **Rapid subscriber expansion** (from 2.3M in 2023 to 10.3M in Q1 2026).\n3. **Strong profitability** (income from operations grew from $469M in 2023 to $4.4B in 2025).\n4. **Trade-off of ARPU for scale** in international markets.\n5. **High capital investment** in satellite infrastructure and R&D.\n\nAll figures are sourced from SpaceX’s unaudited financial disclosures in the provided MD&A and segment reporting tables.',
